<!--
     DTD (Document Type Definition) and XSD (XML Schema Definition) are the grammar for XML
     DTD defines the structure of an XML document
     XSD defines the structure as well as the data of an XML document
     XML Namespaces provide a method to avoid element name conflicts

     XSLT used for transforming XML documents
     XPath used for navigating XML documents
     XPath uses path expressions to select nodes or node-sets in an XML document
     An XPath expression returns either a node-set, a string, a Boolean, or a number
     In XPath, there are seven kinds of nodes:
     element, attribute, text, namespace, processing-instruction, comment, and document nodes

     XQuery used for querying XML documents
     XLink is used to create hyperlinks in XML documents
     XPointer allows links to point to specific parts of an XML document
-->
